FBIS4-56142 "dreeu103__a94024" FBIS-EEU-94-103-A Daily Report 25 May 1994 ANNEX Czech Republic Yugoslav Migrants To Be Granted Refugee Status Yugoslav Migrants To Be Granted Refugee Status AU2505205294 Prague CTK in English 1811 GMT 25 May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2505205294 Prague CTK English BFN [Text] Prague, May 25 (CTK) -- The Czech Government today agreed on putting migrants from ex-Yugoslavia who have been given temporary asylum in this country on an equal footing with refugees. The migrants will in effect be given asylum as well but only until they leave. The decision was based on a document presented by Interior Minister Jan Ruml.
